Clear Explanation of the Website Concept

The website is designed to help students apply to universities more easily and accurately by guiding them through the application process and helping them identify the courses they qualify for based on their academic results.

1. User Registration & Sign-In

Students access the website and sign in or create an account.

During registration, they enter basic personal information such as:

Full name

Contact details

Academic background

Students are also required to upload relevant documents (for example, academic results or certificates).

2. Academic Evaluation

After submitting their academic results, the system evaluates their marks.

The evaluation is done using the current university prospectus and admission requirements.

The system determines which courses the student qualifies for based on their results.

3. University & Course Selection

The student selects the university they wish to apply to.

Courses are presented in a structured way:

First by Faculty

Then by Department

Finally, by the courses the student qualifies for

Students only see courses they are eligible for, reducing confusion and wasted applications.

4. Course Preferences

The student selects:

First choice

Second choice

Third choice (if the university allows a third option)

5. Redirection to University Application Site

Once selections are made, the system redirects the student to the official university application website.

The system automatically fills in basic information that was already provided on the main website (where technically and legally possible).

6. Guided Completion & Error Reduction

For fields that cannot be auto-filled:

The system alerts the student.

It provides clear instructions and examples showing exactly what information to enter, based on the data they already provided.

This minimizes:

Manual typing

Application errors

Incorrect or incomplete submissions

7. Final Submission

The student personally reviews and submits the application on the university‚Äôs website.

After submission, your website steps back and does not interfere further.

Core Purpose of the Website

The main goal of the platform is to:

Help students identify suitable courses they qualify for

Reduce application mistakes

Save time

Make the university application process simpler, smarter, and more accurate

